==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Outwork
<hw>Out*work"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To exceed in
working; to work more or faster than.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outwork</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Outwork
<hw>Out"work`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Fort.)</fld> <def>A
minor defense constructed beyond the main body of a work, as a ravelin,
lunette, hornwork, etc.</def> <rj><au>Wilhelm.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outworth</ent>⟦br⟧
